00:09:10,670 --> 00:09:13,110
You move to cities, and you don't have-- you're right.

206
00:09:13,110 --> 00:09:15,950
So there's obviously something going on, where

207
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:17,880
whatever your situation in the countryside is,

208
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:20,800
you believe it will be improved by moving, or having

209
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:23,950
some members of your family move, to new opportunities in the city.

210
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:25,950
And that's in part because there are more people

211
00:09:25,950 --> 00:09:28,890
on the land than it needs in order to till them.

212
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:29,904
Kennedy?

213
00:09:29,904 --> 00:09:31,695
The reading talked about how the government

214
00:09:31,695 --> 00:09:36,376
was willing to pay for about nine years of education for farmers.

215
00:09:36,376 --> 00:09:39,500
But for other living expenses and other costs, such as textbooks, clothing,

216
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,850
stuff like that, a lot of farmers couldn't afford it.

217
00:09:41,850 --> 00:09:45,160
And in order to improve their standard of living, they tried moving to cities.

218
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,780
And then when they couldn't do that, it led to many problems.

219
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:49,390
OK.

220
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:52,190
Education is improved markedly.

221
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:55,730
In the early years of the People's Republic, before the famine,

222
00:09:55,730 --> 00:10:00,370
rudimentary public health is improved markedly for farmers.

223
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:03,410
So education is there, but it's not free.

224
00:10:03,410 --> 00:10:07,090
If you have no money for textbooks, it's very complicated.

225
00:10:07,090 --> 00:10:10,490
What about health insurance?

226
00:10:10,490 --> 00:10:13,010
Or other forms of social insurance?

227
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:14,900
Are there pensions for farmers?

228
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:15,975
No.

229
00:10:15,975 --> 00:10:17,160
There are no pensions.

230
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:21,680
There's no social-- throughout most of the history of the People's Republic.

231
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:28,400
Despite it being an aspiration, a communist system,

232
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:32,662
there's absolutely no social security system for farmers.

233
00:10:32,662 --> 00:10:34,620
There is one for urban residents-- particularly

234
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:37,320
for those connected with state-owned enterprises.

235
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:39,720
And there is not for farmers.

236
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:42,140
Until very recently, under Premier Wen Jiabao--

237
00:10:42,140 --> 00:10:47,760
introduced an extraordinary plan to give every farmer a rudimentary health care.

238
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:51,120
What you might call a floor, under which you could not fall.

239
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:55,270
At least a foundation of health insurance, which one hopes

240
00:10:55,270 --> 00:10:58,560
will be the building block of a much more grand system.

241
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:00,110
But it's very late in coming.

242
00:11:00,110 --> 00:11:03,863
It really doesn't happen until the 21st century.

